body:
I've always used a peripheral (Microsoft Strategic Commander) for my left hand instead of the keyboard. It has several buttons mapping to spells, items, etc. and most importantly it can slide to move the camera. Now this peripheral has stopped working on PBE, and if that gets pushed to Live I'll be forced to adjust to using strictly the keyboard and mouse.

Switching from buttons to keys isn't too bad, but I'm at a loss regarding what to do with the camera. How do most keyboard users control the camera? I find that using the mouse (edge of screen) is terribly inefficient as I'd like to be moving and aiming skillshots at the same time. I'm so used to controlling the camera with my left hand, so I tried mapping it to WASD. But now I'm making too many mistakes differentiating camera keys from skill keys. How do you people do it?!?

@RIOT please don't disable controllers on Live, and please re-enable them in PBE...
